f=Governance/sentinel/custom/gate-bypass-detection/SKILL.md · in=gate-bypass-detection audits governance failure gate catch itself: decisions met gate criteria never hit gate. scans executed actions spend, commitments, strategic moves against board's gating criteria, flags any qualifying action matching gate ruling decision log, triggers retroactive review root-cause analysis, and, bypasses form pattern, routes process fix configured process owner. · p=gate's integrity measured what goes around it. One bypass accident; pattern process defect (unclear criteria, inconvenient process, intentional workaround) three answers demand different fixes. skill closes loop: qualifying action either ruling, gets retroactive one, exposes gate avoidable. · wu=Triggers: "was gated," "bypass check," "did through board," configured recurring cadence (`bypass_scan_cadence`), typically aligned sweep monthly financial close, executed actions become visible. for: reviewing *content* outputs against constitution (constitution-watch), ruling surfaced decision (board's gate, retroactively). · st:/ Protocol=`Load gate criteria (from board's config + documents: spend gate, commitment/veto scope, constitutional articles) \· -> Scan executed actions in scope (spend records, signed commitments, strategic moves) \· -> Match each qualifying action against the decision log: was there a ruling? \· -> Match found → verified, count it \· -> No match → BYPASS: trigger retroactive review at board + root cause` · h3:Phase Load Criteria=Gate criteria board's, sentinel's: spend approval gate (annualized basis, board-config), locked commitments' scope tests, constitution's articles, escalation multiple. board's thresholds/documents unset, say bypass detection defined gate itself scan against whatever subset exists. · h3:Phase 2 — Scan=Scan executed actions configured scope (`bypass_scan_scope`: ledgers/spend records, contract/commitment stores, decision announcements) period. action, test: *would qualified gate?* qualifying actions proceed; rest out jurisdiction, silently cleared report states scope criteria used. · h3:Phase Match Against Decision Log=qualifying action, look ruling shared decision log (precedent's schema makes search scope/topic/date). Outcomes: · h3:Phase Match Against Decision Log=**VERIFIED** ruling exists covers action. Counted, itemized., **PARTIAL** ruling exists executed action materially exceeds (approved $8K, spent $15K; approved pilot, signed multi-year). Treated bypass difference., **BYPASS** qualifying action, ruling. · h3:Phase Retroactive Review Root Cause=BYPASS/PARTIAL goes board **retroactive review** gate sequence, run late; ruling logged like any (and retroactive ruling REJECT/VIOLATION, operator decides remediation sentinel doesn't unwind actions). Alongside, sentinel runs root cause, distinguishing honestly: · h3:Phase Retroactive Review Root Cause=**Criteria gap** actor plausibly didn't know qualified (unclear threshold, novel action type) fix criteria's clarity., **Process friction** gate known slow/painful enough route around fix process., **Intentional workaround** known avoided escalate operator conduct finding, process finding. · h3:Phase Pattern Process Fix=Repeat bypasses (same actor, action type, route) trigger process-fix proposal routed configured `process_owner_contact` (the operator directly until set): what keeps leaking, root-cause class, concrete change (criteria clarification, threshold adjustment board-config, gate-process simplification). Fix proposals recommendations; adopting them owner's call. · h3:Phase 6 — Log=Scan scope, verified counts, bypasses, retroactive outcomes, root causes, fix proposals logged audit-trail-design's schema, append-only. · of=`## Gate Bypass Scan: [period / scope] \·  \· **Criteria loaded:** [gate/commitments/articles versions] \· **Actions scanned:** [N, qualifying: n] \·  \· \| Action \| Qualified because \| Ruling found? \| Class \| Root cause \|` · pr=**The gate's integrity measured what goes around it.** Verified counts matter much bypasses coverage metric., **Retroactive review, retroactive punishment.** bypassed decision gets gate gotten; remediation conduct operator's., **Root cause before blame.** Criteria gap, friction, workaround different failures different fixes misclassifying friction misconduct teaches people hide better., **Exceeding approval bypass difference.** PARTIAL technicality., **Patterns route process, files.** logged pattern nobody owns fixing surveillance, governance., **Sentinel detects; doesn't rule unwind.** Board rules retroactively; operator remediates. · f=Gate criteria largely unset (board-config unfilled) scan against what exists, lead report criteria gap itself top finding., Action records unavailable/incomplete state coverage honestly; unscanned never verified., Decision log missing/unsearchable qualifying action unmatchable; report bottleneck log, actors., Disputed qualification ("this didn't need gate") dispute goes board readings; sentinel doesn't arbitrate jurisdiction. · b:with Other sentinel Skills=`constitution-watch` reads output *content* against articles; skill reads executed *actions* against gate criteria. Watch hands suspected ungated decisions here; skill hands content concerns back., `audit-trail-design` defines trail skill consumes (action records, decision log) writes to., Boundary board/precedent: gate criteria rulings theirs; sentinel detects absences mismatches. Retroactive rulings board's get logged precedent like any ruling.